      "rationale": "An independent FDA biomedical engineer reviewed all three model setups, including boundary condition application, material assignments, contact definitions, and post-processing scripts. Twelve minor discrepancies identified and corrected before final simulation runs. Final models approved by reviewer. Use error level assessed as Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model physics (linear elastic titanium alloy, frictional contact at screw-rod interface, rigid polyaxial head) must be justified by literature and sensitivity analysis demonstrating that plasticity and geometric nonlinearity are negligible for the QoIs at the load levels tested.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V modeled as linear elastic (E=114 GPa, ν=0.34) consistent with published material data and confirmed by coupon testing. Sensitivity study showed <1.5% QoI change when plasticity (bilinear isotropic hardening) was activated, justifying linear elastic assumption within the F1717 load range. Frictional contact (μ=0.3) validated against torque-off measurements. Model form assessed at Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric dimensions sourced from lot-specific measurements; uncertainty in inputs propagated to QoI uncertainty using Monte Carlo sampling (n≥500).",
      "rationale": "Geometric dimensions measured on five production screws and rods per lot using coordinate measuring machine (CMM); mean values used in nominal model. Material properties from lot certificates supplemented by in-house tensile coupon data (n=6). Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation (n=1000 samples) yielded QoI coefficient of variation <3% for all three quantities, confirming low sensitivity to input variability."
    },
    {
