      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used for validation (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) must be the same quantities used in the COU regulatory submission and must be clinically meaningful.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in the COU regulatory submission and directly correspond to the biomechanical performance endpoints in ASTM F1717. Clinical relevance established: stiffness relates to load sharing with the vertebral column; yield force indicates onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm represents post-yield energy absorption. QoI relevance assessed at Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
