    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted on the basis that the single-condition F1717 protocol is the regulatory standard for this device class and that all three QoIs show strong agreement (maximum E/uval = 0.84) with negligible sensitivity to loading rate. The FEA modeling framework is assessed as credible for its intended use in the COU regulatory submission.",
